        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Concerning the Águila and the Diario del Congreso, Mexico.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Mexico </placeName><date when="1823-11-15">15 Novem, 1823</date></p>
<p><persName>Mr. Stephen F. Austin</persName></p>

<p>Sir, <persName>Mr. Lorrain</persName> requests me to say that he has not sent you the
<placeName>Águila </placeName>for some time in consequence of having ceased to print it.
We are now jointly engaged in printing and publishing the "Diario
del Congreso, we forward the first thirteen numbers by this mail
(post paid) and shall continue to forward them regularly so long as
you remain in <placeName>Texas</placeName>. If you can procure news or <persName>subscribers </persName>will
be obliged to you for cither; the latter must pay in advance.</p>

<p><persName>James Hepburn</persName>.</p>

        </div1>
    </body>
